            <a name="usage"/>
            <subsection name="jPBC Usage">
                <p>
                    To use jPBC it is enough to add to your classpath the following jars:
                    <ol type="1">
                        <li>
                            <tt>jpbc_2.0.0-api.jar</tt>
                            and
                        </li>

                        <li>
                            <tt>jpbc_2.0.0-plaf.jar</tt>.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Note that the jars files can be found in the distro package under the <tt>jars</tt> folder.
                </p>
            </subsection>
            <subsection name="PBC Wrapper Usage">
                <p>
                    To use the PBC wrapper you need to compile the shared library
                    that enables the communication between PBC and jPBC. Please,
                    find
                    <a href="./docs/pbcwrapper.html">here</a>
                    the instructions to compile the shared library.
                    <br/>
                    Then, to use the wrapper include the following jars:
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <tt>jpbc_2.0.0-pbc.jar</tt>
                        and
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <tt>jna-3.1.0.jar</tt>.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </subsection>
            <subsection name="Multilinear Maps Usage">
                <p>
                    Finally, to use the
                    <a href="docs/multimaps.html">Multilinear Maps over the Integers</a>,
                    include the following jar:
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <tt>jpbc_2.0.0-mm.jar</tt>.
                    </li>
                </ol>
